(6,	'Global Chocolate Beer Market: Information By Type (Chocolate Ale Beer, Chocolate Lager Beer, Chocolate Stout Beer), by Packaging Material (Glass, Paper, Metal), and by Distribution Channel (On-Premise, Off-Premise)—Forecast Till 2027',	0,	1,	8,	8,	NULL,	'<p><strong>Market Scenario</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The global chocolate beer market is expected to grow at a CAGR of 10.3% during the forecast period 2021&ndash;2027.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chocolate beer is made up of chocolate, especially the dark chocolate or cocoa which is gaining popularity amongst chocolate lovers. It is made in different ways such as by adding chocolate to the brewing process or by using chocolate malt. The style is generally in the form of a stout. Additionally, the flavor of chocolate stout is rich and tasty and is aromatic in smell.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The increasing demand for flavored beer in young population, is driving the growth of the market. The growing demand for the product from developing countries is one of the major factor driving the market growth during the forecast period 2019&ndash;2026. Additionally, increasing disposable income is rising the consumption of beer which is boosting the growth of market. Additionally, health advantages associated with the consumption of dark chocolate and moderate amount of beer will propel the growth of market. The rising number of craft breweries is another factor emerging the market to grow. Furthermore, the increasing number of pubs and restaurants is positively affecting the chocolate beer market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Market Segmentation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The global chocolate beer market is segmented into type, packaging material, distribution channel, and region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Based on the type, the market is segmented into chocolate ale beer, chocolate lager beer, chocolate stout beer, and other chocolate beer. Amongst type, chocolate lager beer segment is expected to dominate the market owing to the constantly growing demand for lager beer and flavored lager beer. Moreover, leaning trend towards night life in lounges and pubs is influencing the market growth. Chocolate ale beer segment is anticipated to account for optimum share of the market owing to new launch of ale products in the developed region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of packaging material, the market is segmented into glass, paper, metal, and others. Glass segment is forecasted to gross major share of the market owing to the increased use of glass packaging material for the packaging of beer and chocolate beer due to safety of the packaging and minimal risk of incompatibility with the stored product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk520446687\"></a>On the basis of distribution channel, the market is segmented into on-premises and off-premises. On-premises segment is expected to account for major share of the market owing to the growing number of lounges and pubs in the developed and developing regions. Moreover, bundle offers and discounts offered by the lounges and pubs are attracting the growing number of customers in the last few years. Off-premises segment is anticipated to account for significant share of the market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regional Analysis</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Geographically, the global chocolate beer market is bifurcated into four major region such as North America, Europe, Asia Pacific (APAC), and Latin America and Middle East &amp; Africa (LAMEA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Europe is expected to dominate the market during the forecast period 2019&ndash;2026 owing to the increasing consumption of flavored beers is driving the growth of the market. For instance, in December 2016, European brewing sector is on the way of prosperity. Beer is experiencing the renaissance in Europe with the presence of 7,500 breweries. Consumption and production are year-on-year increasing from 2014&ndash;2015 of 1% in consumption and 1.4% in production.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>North America is expecting a significant growth owing to the increasing demand for the chocolate beer products especially in U.S. and Canada. For instance, in July 2018, A Canadian Company named as Province Brands developing the world&rsquo;s first beer called as cannabis beer brewed from the marijuana plant. This beer hits you very quickly, which is not common for a marijuana edible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asia Pacific (APAC) is expected to experience a strong growth during the forecasted period owing to the increasing expenditure and standard of living is driving the market growth. Increasing popularity of chocolate beer among the consumers especially in the countries such as China and India which offers high potential growth for players is propelling the growth of market in APAC. According to World Health organization (WHO), Chinese population consumes a wide range of alcoholic beverages. Additionally, it is estimated that China is one of the largest beer producing countries in the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk520446662\"></a>LAMEA is expected to have the firm growth during the forecasted period owing to the low expenditure, developing standard of living, and limited consumption of alcoholic beverages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	NULL,	10,	'global-chocolate-beer-market',	NULL,	1,	NULL,	NULL),
(7,	'Global Textured Soy Protein Market: Information by Type (Non-GMO, Conventional, Organic, Other Types), Source (Soy Protein Concentrates, Soy Protein Isolates, Soy Flour), Application—Forecast till 2026',	0,	1,	8,	8,	NULL,	'<p>Global textured soy protein market accounted for around USD 2,150 million in 2020 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 11.5% during the forecast period, 2021&ndash;2027.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Soy proteins are rich in all nine essential amino acids and provide many benefits in maintaining healthy diet. These are used by manufacturers to promote flavor &amp; moisture retention and also used in enhancing the texture of several foods such as peanut butter, cheese and frozen desserts. Soy protein is easily digestible. Furthermore, it contains zero cholesterol and is lactose free. Texturized soy products have variety of applications and used as an alternative source of protein for a wide variety of people. Textured soy protein can be added to meat as extenders or can be used as simulated meat analogs. In addition, along with animal derived proteins usage of soy proteins is increasing among athletes to fulfil the daily protein requirement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rising consumer demands to maintain healthy diet and increasing meat prices have led to the high demand of textured soy protein. To cater to the increasing demand of non- meat products major manufacturers are engaged in development of high quality products which provide high nutritional benefits. For instance, Cargill, a global provider of food and agricultural products offers Prosante textured soy flour. This is high quality textured soy protein, which is cost effective and offers several health benefits such as low in fat, maintains moisture and stimulates foods natural texture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Growing vegetarian population looking for alternatives to meat and low cost have propmted the consumers in developed countries to prefer theses products. In addition, increasing chronic disease in developing countries has pushed the demand of healthy products, which is contributing significantly to the market growth. Manufacturers have noticed this paradigm shift in demand of these products from emerging economies and have started to tap these regions. For instance, in November 2017, Archer Daniels Midland Company, an ingredient giant have started selling soy products from its Brazilian plant to the Middle East &amp; Africa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Segmental Insights</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Global textured soy protein market is segmented by type, source and application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By type, the market is segmented into non-GMO, conventional and organic. Non-GMO segment is expected to grow at the fastest CAGR as it is most commercially available as compared to other sources.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By source, the textured soy protein market is segmented into soy protein concentrates, soy protein isolates and soy flour. Soy protein concentrate is expected to hold the largest market share. It contains high protein and is preferred choice of source of food manufactures. High demand from meat industry is also boosting the growth of the source segment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk4589816\"></a>Based on application, textured soy protein market is segmented into food and feed. The food is sub-segmented into meat substitutes, dairy alternatives, infant nutrition, bakery products and cereals &amp; snack. The food segment can grow at the highest CAGR during the forecast period on account of increasing consumer demands for high protein products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regional Insights</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Geographically, the global textured soy protein market is segmented into four regions: North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, and Latin America and the Middle East &amp; Africa (LAMEA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk4589835\"></a>North America textured soy protein market is likely to lead due to increasing demand from U.S. and Canada and high production of soybean in the region. For instance, as per United States Department of Agriculture, National Agricultural Statistics Service (USDA-NASS) Crop Production 2017, the U.S. is produced another record soybean crop at 120.6 MMT. This was a 3% increase as compared to crop of 117.0 MMT in 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Europe is likely to emerge as the second largest market globally. This can be attributed to the increasing consumption of textured soy protein in the region. Presence of soy processing units in the region is strengthening the growth of the market. For instance, Sojaprotein is the largest soybean processing factory in Serbia with processed capacity of 250,000 tons per year. It is also one of the most important soybean processors in Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asia Pacific is expected to witness significant growth on account of presence of large vegetarian population. In addition, increasing consumption of vegetable proteins in food products is driving the growth in the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LAMEA is expected to witness steady growth in the industrial sector. Brazil and Argentina in South America are the major soybean producer countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key Players:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the key players in the global textured soy protein market are Cargill, ADM, Wilmar International, DowDuPont, Bremil Group, Victoria Group, Linyi Shansong Biological Products, Crown Soya Protein Group, Shandong Yuxin Bio-Tech, Hung Yang Foods and Sonic Biochem.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Our Report Covers</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Historical inferences, findings &amp; analysis of the market from 2016 to 2018</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Projections and performance forecast analysis for the future from 2019 to 2026</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Production and consumption point of view (POV) analysis</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Market drivers, restraint and opportunity analysis, to define market dynamics covering industry, regulatory, innovation, technological &amp; pricing trends</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Comprehensive competitive landscape mapping with recent development covering market leadership, competency, sustainability, and prospects</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Textured Soy Protein Market Segmentation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Type</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Non-GMO</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Conventional</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Organic</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Other Types</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Source</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Soy Protein Concentrates</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Soy Protein Isolates</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Soy Flour</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Application</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Food</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Meat Substitutes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dairy Alternatives</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Infant Nutrition</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bakery Products</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Cereal &amp; Snacks</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Other Food Applications</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Feed</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regions Covered:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>North America</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Europe</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Asia-Pacific</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>LAMEA</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	NULL,	10,	'global-textured-soy-protein-market',	NULL,	1,	NULL,	NULL),
(8,	'Global Wireless Charging Market, By Technology (Inductive charging system, Resonant charging system, Microwave wireless charging system, Radio Frequency charging system and others), By Application (Consumer electronics, Automotive, Industrial, Healthcare, Aerospace & Defense), BY Standard (Wireless Power Consortium (WPC), Power Matters Alliance (PMA), Alliance for Wireless Power (A4WP), Open Dots), By Product type (Transmitter, Receiver), By Transmission Range (Short, Medium, Long), By Distribution Channel (After sales market & Original Equipment Store), By Geography – Global Industry Analysis and Industry Forecasts till 2028',	0,	1,	9,	8,	NULL,	'<p>The Global Wireless Charging Market is estimated USD 7.2 billion in 2020 and anticipated to reach USD 66.57 billion by 2027 at a CAGR of 41.3% during the forecast period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wireless charging is a process of electric power transfer from charging device/s or node to receiver devices powered by battery/ies and also equipment/s electrically without tangible wired power transfer. Wireless Charging Equipment consists of two components a charging system (Transmitter) which transmits electric power through the electromagnetic field and a Device Inbuilt Receiver which charges the battery. However, it has many industrial applications such as electric vehicles, handheld terminals, contactless charging of subsea vehicles, factory automation, etc. Industrial applications of wireless charging demand the workability of portable equipment and its wireless charging system in the harsh conditions. With the absence of wired power transmission, a wireless charging system can be impregnable to the industrial environment. Moreover, due to the absence of wired power transfer, the usage of wireless charging is safe from hazards such as electrocution &amp; fire escalation because of stray spark during connecting &amp; disconnecting wired power transfer cable. In terms of applications, consumer electronics is the dominant industry in the market due to rapid and efficient consumer electronics manufacturing. Manufacturers have been aiming mobile &amp; rechargeable consumer electronics such as laptops and smartphones.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of technology, the global wireless charging market is segmented into the inductive charging system, resonant charging system, microwave wireless charging system, radiofrequency charging system, and others. Based on the type of application, consumer electronics, automotive, industrial, healthcare, aerospace &amp; defense are the categories which this market caters to. Based on the type of standard in which the wireless charging system available is categorized as Wireless Power Consortium (WPC), Power Matters Alliance (PMA), Alliance for Wireless Power (A4WP), open dots. On the basis of product type, this market is bifurcated into the transmitter and receiver. On the basis of the transmission range of the charging system, this market provides products in these categories such as short, medium and long. Based on the distribution channel type, this market is segmented into modern retail stores, specialty stores, after-sales market, and original equipment store. On the basis of geography, this market is categorized into North America (NA), Europe Union (EU), Asia-Pacific (APAC), Latin America (LA), Middle East &amp; Africa (MEA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Increased Mobility, ease of handling, rise in disposable income throughout the world, expanding expenditure on electronic gadgets, flexibility, protection against electric shocks, a convenient power transfer method for the Internet of Things (IoT) proliferation are stimulating the demand and market growth. Moreover, wireless charging technology integration in automobiles, embedded wireless charging in consumer electronics (such as wearable devices, tablets, and smartphones) and increased healthcare segment applications are driving awareness in the market about wireless power transmission technology. The aforementioned factors are the growth drivers for the global wireless charging market. Longer duration of charging, limited portability, lack of standardization of technology, limited range per charge (in case of electric vehicles application), charging potentials are the factors restraining the growth in this market. Increased IoT adoption &amp; smart devices, technological advancement in wireless charging systems across the sectors, adoption of wireless charging &amp; electric vehicle in automobiles, rising infrastructural developments (such as smart cities in developed &amp; developing countries, wireless charging stations for electric vehicles across the globe), declining conventional methods (such as reliance on wired power transfer &amp; fossil fuels in case of vehicles) are the factors that bring numerous opportunities for the market growth. Cost of up-gradation to wireless technology from conventional methodologies across sectors in developed &amp; developing countries and also across the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>North America holds prominence as compared to other regions in the market with expected to grow nearly at CAGR 14% during the forecast period. This region is driven by a range of innovative breakthroughs in the wireless power transfer. For example, the launch of the Q4 wireless bundle to Q3 wireless chargers which provides optimum charging speed coupled with compactivity and portable size was witnessed in the region. Furthermore, the rising demand for electric vehicles has stimulated manufacturers to invest in safer &amp; efficient charging systems. The European market is predicted to grow a CAGR of 28.69% approx. which is 3rd highest market revenue in this market during the forecast period. Factors such as high urban penetration, high adoption of wireless power transmission, the fastest-growing electric vehicle wireless charging market &amp; related infrastructure and huge scope in medical equipment are stimulating potential market growth opportunities for the market expansion. The Asia Pacific is the largest revenue generator for the global market which is expected to grow with a CAGR of 42.94% approx... APAC is mainly segmented on the basis of applications, technology, and components. Various factors such as increased penetration of smartphones, the large consumer electronics base, rising wireless computing devices adoption are primary growth drivers. Moreover, suppliers for ICs required in wireless power transmission are developing miniaturized &amp; high energy transfer efficient ICs. Amongst other regional markets, China is leading the market but also Japan, India, South Korea, and Australia are the major revenue contributors to the regional market. Middle East &amp; Africa is expected to grow at slow &amp; steady CAGR % but has higher revenue market share as compared to Latin America. As in the Middle East region, the growth in the market driven by Gulf Countries &amp; heavy investment by Israel but in Africa, the market is in the nascent stages of adoption. Latin America is expected to grow in the forecast period, as it lacks the adoption of wireless power transmission into the masses. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These are the key players in the market which drive the market demand such as Qualcomm Inc., Oregon Scientific Inc., Integrated Device Technology Inc., Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd., Leggett &amp; Platt Inc., Texas Instrument Inc., Powermat Technologies Ltd., Witricity Corporation, Murata Manufacturing Co. Ltd., Energizer Holdings Inc., Convenient Power HK Ltd., Mojo Mobility Inc., NXP Semiconductor N.V., TDK Corporation, Semtech Corporation.</p>\r\n',	NULL,	10,	'global-wireless-charging-market',	NULL,	1,	NULL,	NULL),
(9,	'Global Semiconductor Lasers Market, By Product Type (Fiber Optic Lasers (FOL), Vertical Cavity Surface Emitting Lasers (VCSEL), Compact Disc Lasers (CDL), High Power Diode Lasers (HPDL), Blue Laser, Infrared Laser and others), By Application, By Material used, By Geography – Global Industry Analysis and Industry Forecasts till 2027',	0,	1,	10,	8,	NULL,	'<p>Semiconductor Laser (also called Laser Diode) described as a device due to which laser oscillation occurs when electric charge flows through a semiconductor. It has similarities with LED Mechanism. The industrial &amp; commercial use of laser diodes has brought new opportunities due to its compact &amp; small size, higher efficiency as compared to the conventional lasers, power-saving characteristics, optical characteristics, and ruggedness. The global semiconductor laser market is anticipated to grow from USD 7.12 billion in 2019 to 14.53 billion by 2030 at a CAGR of approx. 6.7%. A concentrated monochromatic light beam emitted by a compact-size semiconductor laser which is a natural digital data transmitter and interfaced with optical fibers communication. Semiconductor lasers have an application such as</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of product type, the global semiconductor laser market is segmented into fiber-optic lasers (FOL), vertical-cavity surface-emitting lasers (VCSEL), compact disc lasers (CDL), high power diode lasers (HPDL), blue laser, infrared laser, and others. Based on application, this market is categorized into optical storage devices lithography, display, printing, defense, telecom &amp; communication, industrial application, healthcare, sensors, and others. On the basis of material used, this market is divided into gallium arsenide (GaAs), aluminum gallium arsenide (AlGaAs), gallium phosphide (GaP), indium gallium phosphide (InGaP), gallium nitride (GaN), indium gallium arsenide (InGaAs) and others. On the basis of geography, this market is segmented into North America (NA), Europe (EU), Asia-Pacific (APAC), Latin America (LA) and Middle East &amp; Africa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_GoBack\"></a><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Highly efficient semiconductor lasers, Laser Fibre market expansion, Dedicated assembly, lower packaging error tolerance, rise in healthcare sector usage and growing demand in the defence sector are the factors to drive the growth in the global laser diode market. Furthermore, the favorable regulations regarding the usage of semiconductors in 3D printing for the healthcare sector are anticipated to throttle the market growth. However, less reliability &amp; testing, delicate design, low packaging tolerance error hamper market growth. Furthermore, the regulations favorable to the usage of semiconductor lasers also restrain the usage of it in prosthetic organs&rsquo; building and other life science-based solicitations. Moreover, high demand for semiconductor laser for data storage applications across industries. However, functional shortfalls &amp; efficiency of semiconductor lasers are expected to pose challenges for market growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>North America is anticipated to be a symbol of the matured market which holds major market share during the forecast period. Factors such as increment in advanced infrastructural development, high demand for technological advanced medical devices in the healthcare sector will drive the market growth in the markets. North America and Europe are predicted to lose a share of the semiconductor laser market to APAC. Asia-Pacific has the largest share of the market and is expected to experience the highest CAGR due to the higher manufacturing sector boom and industrialization. APAC is anticipated to experience demand growth in the market owing to technological solicitations and associated technologies. Factors such as the growth of numerous sectors due to government policies and investments, semiconductor industrial growth, low cost of manufacturing, cheap labor which will stimulate the material processing and lithography demand to cater to the demand of the SL market. Latin America and Middle East &amp; Africa are predicted to witness the steady growth in the market due to emerging economies and growing industrialization during the forecast period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key players in the semiconductor laser market are IPG Photonics Corporation, Coherent Inc., ASML Holdings N.V., Newport Corporation, Sharp Corporation, Trumpf GmbH + Co. KG, Sumitomo Electric Industries Ltd., Rofin-Sinar Technologies Inc., Hans Laser Technology Industry Group Co. Ltd., and Axcel Photonics Inc.</p>\r\n',	NULL,	10,	'global-semiconductor-lasers-market',	NULL,	1,	NULL,	NULL),
(10,	'Global Foley Catheters Market: Information By Product Type (Two-way, Three-way, Four-way, Temperature Sensor Integrated Catheter), By Material Type (Silicone, Latex, Teflon Coated Latex, Silicone Elastomer Coated Latex, Hydrophilic Polymer Coated Latex, Others), By End User—Forecast till 2028',	0,	1,	12,	8,	NULL,	'<p>Global foley catheters market accounted for approximately USD 1,710.4 million in 2020 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 6.0% during the forecast period, 2021&ndash;2028/.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Foley catheter is a flexible tube passed through urethra and into bladder to drain urine . Foley catheters are typically used in patients suffering from prostate hypertrophy, narrowing of the urethra, prostate cancer, and bladder dysfunction. Prostate cancer is the most common cancer types among men. As per NIH statistics, prostate cancer incidence among the U.S. men can be estimated at nearly 174,650 in 2019. Based on 2014 &ndash; 2016 data, NIH further estimates that nearly 11.6% of men are at a risk of developing prostate cancer at any point in their lifetime.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Increasing prevalence of chronic diseases along with growing number of surgical procedures globally is boosting the Foley catheters market. However, effects of Foley catheters on sexual function and urinating after the removal of device is hindering the market growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Segmental Insights</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The global Foley catheters market is segmented based on product type, material type, and end user.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Based on product type, the Foley catheters market is bifurcated into two-way, three-way, four-way, and temperature sensor integrated catheter. Two-way catheters are expected to grow at the fastest CAGR over the forecast period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By material type, the Foley catheters market is categorized into silicone, latex, Teflon coated latex, silicone elastomer coated latex, hydrophilic polymer coated latex, others. Silicone elastomer coated latex catheters is projected to grow with the fastest GACR during forecasted period. This can be attributed to high flexibility, reduced urethral irritation, and diminished encrustation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Based on end&ndash;users, the market is categorized into hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, and medical research centers. Hospitals segment accounted for the majority of the market share in 2018 owing to rise in the number of surgical treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regional Insights</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Geographically, the global Foley catheters market is segmented into four regions: North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, and Latin America and the Middle East &amp; Africa (LAMEA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>North America Foley catheters market is projected to dominate over the forecast period due to presence of advanced diagnostic facilities as well as technologically developed surgical facilities. Furthermore, high healthcare expenditure, increasing prevalence of prostate cancer, and high number of invasive surgeries in this region is further boosting the market growth. For instance as per NIH statistics, nearly 3.1 million U.S. men were living with prostate cancer in 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Europe is likely to emerge as the second largest Foley catheters market followed. Presence of key market players developing technologically advanced catheters is one of the key factors for the market growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asia Pacific is the fastest growing region owing to incresing number of urological surgeries and subsequently rising demand for the Foley catheters in the region. Increasing prevalence of various chronic disease including prostate cancer in emerging countries such as China, India further drives the market growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Emergence of medical tourism in the Latin American countries such as Brazil, Mexico, and Costa Rica offer signifi