(12,	'Global cochlear implants market: by fitting type (unilateral implantation, bilateral implantation), end-user (hospitals & clinics, ambulatory surgical centers, research & academic institutes)—Forecast till 2026',	0,	1,	12,	8,	NULL,	'<p><strong>Market Scenario</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The global cochlear implants market size was valued around USD 1,935 million in 2020 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 9.7% over the forecast period 2021-2027.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk520468794\"></a>Cochlear implant is an electronic medical device which is used to replace the function of inner ear when it gets damaged. As compared to other hearing aids, it is used to bypass the damaged hair cells of the inner ear (cochlea) to facilitate the transmission of sound signals to brain. Moreover, these implants are mainly used for patients suffering from average-to-extreme hearing loss in both ears. Additionally, it can improve communication and quality of life for the people with severe hearing loss who receive little advantage from hearing aids. Therefore, cochlear implants in both ears (bilateral) are considered as a standard care for the treatment of severe hearing loss, mainly for infants and children who are learning to speak and process language. According to World Health Organization (WHO), it is estimated that over 5% of the global population or 466 million people suffer from disabling hearing loss. Additionally, by 2050, over 900 million people will suffer from disabling hearing loss.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk514246569\"></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Technological improvement in cochlear implants to make the device more efficient and user-friendly can propel the growth of the market during the forecast period 2018&ndash;2025. Moreover, rising in geriatric population contributing to the huge patient pool, growing in product customization, and introduction of rechargeable cochlear implants are the factors boosting the growth of the market. According to National Institutes of Health, the global older population is growing at the remarkable rate. It is estimated that 8.5 percent of people globally (617 million) are aged 65 and over. Furthermore, increasing government support and healthcare expenditure have fueled the market growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additionally, new improvements for developing innovative next generation sound processors and developing potential markets provide the opportunities for the growth of the market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Market segmentation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk514246706\"></a>The global cochlear implant market is segmented into fitting type, end-user, and region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of fitting type, the market is segmented into unilateral implantation and bilateral implantation. Unilateral implantation is expected to major market share owing to lower cost as compared to bilateral implant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of the end-user segment, the market is segmented into hospitals &amp; clinics, ambulatory surgical centers, research &amp; academic institutes, and others. Hospitals &amp; clinics is expected to generate major market share during forecast period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regional analysis</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The global cochlear implant market is mainly bifurcated into four regions such as North America, Europe, Asia Pacific (APAC), and Latin America and Middle East &amp; Africa (LAMEA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>North America is expected to hold the major share for the market during the forecast period 2018&ndash;2025 owing to the huge presence of patients suffering from hearing loss. According to the National Institute on Deafness and Other Communication Disorders (NIDCD), it is estimated that about 2 to 3 out of every 1,000 children in the United States are born with a noticeable level of hearing loss in one or both ears. Additionally, around 15% of American adults (37.5 million) aged 18 and over suffer from some trouble hearing. Increasing government support for the research and development, well-developed technology, and high healthcare expenditure is driving the growth of the market especially in the U.S.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Europe is estimated to be the second largest region owing to large number of population suffering from the hearing defects well developed healthcare infrastructure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Furthermore, according to the comprehensive Spanish study, it is predicted that in Spain about 3,800 people have cochlear implant. Among these, 61 percent are children with hearing loss, and 39 percent are adults. Apart from this, Huge number of leading players of cochlear implant presence in this region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asia Pacific is predicted to be the fastest growing region due to the growing needs for better devices, rapidly improving technology, and presence of large patient pools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LAMEA holds the least share due to the presence of poor and slow developing countries. Additionally, the cochlear implants are more costly and due to poor economic condition, the market is slowing down especially in this region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key Players</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In September 2017, Cochlear Ltd.&nbsp;launched nucleus, which is world&#39;s smallest and lightest behind-the-ear cochlear implant sound processor, it control hearing process and connect with the technology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a name=\"_Hlk514246725\"></a>Some of the major players included in the global cochlear implant market are Cochlear Ltd. (Australia), MED-EL GmbH (Austria), Sonova Holding AG (Switzerland), William Demant Holding A/S (Denmark), Starkey (U.S.), Nurotron Biotechnology Co. Ltd. (U.S.), Widex (Denmark), Advanced Bionics AG (Switzerland), and Oticon Medical (U.S.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why to buy this report right now?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our report covers the cochlear implant market market insights, focusing on recent development in the market in different region and development strategies of the companies. Moreover, following sections are specifically covered in the report.<br />\r\n&bull; Definitive Market Data<br />\r\n&bull; cochlear implant market Analysis<br />\r\n&bull; Competitive Analysis<br />\r\n&bull; Recent Opportunities in the Market<br />\r\n&bull; 6-7 year performance forecasts: major segments covering top product type, end-user application, and geographies<br />\r\n&bull; Market Share Analysis<br />\r\n&bull; Potential Venture Avenues</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cochlear Implants Market</strong><strong> Segmentation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Fitting Type:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><a name=\"_Hlk513628994\"></a>Unilateral Implantation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bilateral Implantation</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Product:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><a name=\"_Hlk513629010\"></a>Cochlear Implant System</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Accessories &amp; Upgrades</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By End-User:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hospitals &amp; Clinics</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Ambulatory Surgical Centers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Research &amp; Academic Institutes</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Others</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>By Region</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>North America</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Europe</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Asia Pacific</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Latin America and Middle East &amp; Africa</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	NULL,	10,	'global-cochlear-implants-market',	NULL,	1,	NULL,	NULL),
(13,	'Global Anthrax Treatment Market: Information by Route of Transmission (Cutaneous Anthrax, Inhalation Anthrax, Gastrointestinal Anthrax and Injection Anthrax), Drug Class (Fluoroquinolone, Tetracycline) and End – use—forecast till 2027',	0,	1,	13,	8,	NULL,	'<p>Global Anthrax Treatment market accounted for over USD 288.65 million in 2019 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 7.7 % during the forecast period, 2021&ndash;2027.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anthrax therapeutics consists of medications used to treat infections caused by <em>Bacillus Anthracis </em>transmitted by livestock. The common routes of anthrax transmission are cutaneous, inhalation, injection, and gastrointestinal. The spores of <em>Bacillus Anthracis when activated, release </em>toxic substances that can cause swelling, internal bleeding, and tissue death.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The incidence of anthrax has reduced in developed countries on account of improved industrial hygiene and vaccination. However, the incidence is high among under developed or developing countries wherein routine vaccination programs against anthrax does not exists. Development of anthrax therapeutics has gained traction post September 2001 bioterrorism incidence in the U.S.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Growing funding for R&amp;D in the area of anthrax therapeutics and various strategies developed by the government agencies for stockpiling are the key factors driving the anthrax treatment market. Anthim injection, Anthrasil, Biothrax, Ciproflaxacin, and Doxycycline are among few of the FDA approved therapies for the treatment of anthrax. However, high cost of diagnosis, treatment and vaccines hinder the growth of market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Segmental Insights</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Global anthrax treatment market is segmented by route of transmission, drug class, and end &ndash; use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By route of transmission, the market is segmented into cutaneous anthrax, inhalation anthrax, gastrointestinal anthrax, and injection anthrax. In most of the reported cases, cutaneous route is the common most transmission route, accounting for more than 80% of the cases. As per European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control, in 2014, nine cases of cutaneous anthrax were reported from Hungary. However, the transmission from gastrointestinal route is also rising owing to the consumption of raw uncooked meat. In the recent years, few cases of injection, are also reported.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By treatment type, the anthrax treatment market is segmented into antibiotics, monoclonal antibodies, others. New drug approvals is the key factor attributing to the market growth. In March 2016, U.S. FDA announced the approval of obiltoxaximab injection, &lsquo;Anthim&rsquo;, for the treatment of inhalation anthrax. In November 2015, Emergent BioDefense Operations Lansing LLC announced the FDA approval for its Anthrax Vaccine Adsorbed, BioThrax. Issuance of emergency dispensing information, by U.S. FDA is also boosting the market growth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Based on end use, anthrax treatment market is segmented into hospitals and clinics, ambulatory surgery centers, government agencies, and others. Government agencies accounted for the largest revenue share. Nearly, 86.7% of the product sales of Emergent Biosolutions, Inc. were to the government agencies. Altimune, Inc. , another important market player, stated that all the company revenue has been derived from grants and U.S. government contracts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regional Insights</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Geographically, the global anthrax treatment market is segmented into four regions: North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, and Latin America and the Middle East &amp; Africa (LAMEA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>North America accounted for the largest revenue share in 2018 owing to the high government funding, supportive strategies such as National Stockpile Strategy, and presence of the key market players innovating anthrax treatment therapies in this region. Another example of supportive strategy includes, a vaccination campaign, Anthrax Vaccine Immunization Program, conducted by the U.S. Department of Defense, wherein over 3.2 million people received more than 13.1 million doses of vaccines between 1998 to 2015.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asia Pacific one of the key regions in terms of the market growth. Anthrax is one of the common endemics in China and in the recent years number of anthrax outbreaks have been reported in China. Since the start of 2018, nearly 106 cases of anthrax were reported in the country. Various government initiatives aimed at mitigating the risk of Anthrax are expected to drive the market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anthrax is a rear disease in the Europe, with only a few number of cases reported per year. In 2014, nearly 16 cases of anthrax were reported in EU/EEA countries. To mitigate the risk of anthrax related bioterrorism, European Commission formed a preparedness and response program for attacks by biological and chemical agents (BICHAT) in 2002. In 2012, the U.S. agreed to fund USD 6.5 million UK&rsquo;s Health Protection Agency to support the work on anthrax vaccine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LAMEA is presently in the nascent phase of the market growth. However, presence of large number of population in contact with the livestock represent favorable market opportunities in the coming years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key Players:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the key players in the global anthrax market are Glaxo SmithKline Pharmaceuticals Ltd., Elusys Therapeutics, Inc., Emergent BioSolutions, Inc., Altimune, Inc.,Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd., Novartis AG, Bayer AG.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Our Report Covers</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Historical inferences, findings &amp; a