(14,	'Antibacterial drugs market: information by drug class (	B-lactams, quinolones, macrolides, tetracycline, aminoglycoside, sulfonamide, phenicols), route of administration, distribution channel— forecast till 2026',	0,	1,	13,	8,	NULL,	'<p><strong>Market Overview</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The global antibacterial drugs market is expected to value around USD 53,148 million in 2020 and with registered CAGR of 2.2% during forecast period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Antibacterial drugs is a type of antimicrobial substance active against bacteria and it is used for fighting bacterial infections. Antibiotic medications are widely used to kill or inhibit the bacterial growth. Increasing prevalence of bacterial infection across the globe is driving the growth of the market. Bacterial infections may be affect throat, lungs, skin, bowel and many others parts of the body and bacterial infection some are mild, and some are severe. Furthermore, rising incidence of carrion&#39;s disease, rheumatic fever, bacterial pneumonia, leprosy, and tetanus is driving the growth of the market. Apart increasing geriatric patient, changing lifestyle, modernization is weaker immunity is influence antibacterial infections.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Segmentation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The globally, the antibacterial drug market is segmented by drug class, route of administration, and distribution channel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of drug class, the antibacterial drug market is segmented into Beta-lactams, Quinolones, Macrolides, Tetracycline, Aminoglycoside, Sulfonamide, Phenicols, and Others. Beta-lactams is expected to hold major market share during forecast period owing to broad spectrum antibiotics active against <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gram-positive\" target=\"Gram-positive\">gram-positive</a>&nbsp; and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gram-negative_bacteria\" target=\"Gram-negative bacteria\">gram-negative</a>&nbsp; antibiotics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Based on route of administration, the market is segmented into enteral, parenteral and others. Enteral dosage form is expected to hold major market share because this route is simple and convenient that improves the patient compliance and it is cost effective.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the basis of distribution channel, the antibacterial drug market is segmented into hospital pharmacies, drug stores and retail pharmacies and online sales. Hospital pharmacies is expected to hold major market share owing to high volume of patient visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regional Analysis</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Geographically, the antibacterial drug market is segmented into Asia Pacific, North America, Europe, (LAMEA).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Asia Pacific is expected to be witness significantly grow over the forecast period. This is attributed to high burden of bacterial infection disease such as rheumatic fever, bacterial pneumonia, leprosy, and tetanus. According to the government of India, around 920136 people suffered from pneumonia in 2016. Moreover, poor public health infrastructure is boosting the growth of the market. Apart from this, rising incomes and the unregulated sale of generic version of antibiotics is boosting the growth of the antibacterial market.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>North America is expected to hold major market share during forecast period. Growing incidence of bacterial vaginosis in U.S. is driving the growth of the market. For instance, according to World Health Organization, in 2016, approximately 21 million American women believed to affect by bacterial vaginosis. Moreover, increasing geriatric patient in this region is supporting the growth of the market. Furthermore increasing incidence of preterm labor treatment is influencing demand of B-lactam antibiotics during forecast period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Europe is expected to hold second major market share during forecast period owing to increasing prevalence of different bacterial infection in this region. Growing number of incidence of flu, hep